      "text": [
        "2237 - وَرُوِيَ: \"أَنَّ صَلَاةَ فَرِيضَةٍ خَيْرٌ مِنْ عِشْرِينَ حَجَّةً، وَحَجَّةٌ خَيْرٌ مِنْ بَيْتٍ مَمْلُوءٍ ذَهَبًا يُتَصَدَّقُ بِهِ حَتَّى يُنْفَى\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2237 - It has been narrated: \"One obligatory prayer is better than twenty Hajj, and one Hajj is better than a house filled with gold given in charity until nothing remains.\""
        ]
      }
    },
    "verse_translations": [
      "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications"
